article.description: — Brion Whitley came off the bench to score 14 points to guide Southern to a 73-64 win over Alabama A&M on Saturday.
article.headline: Whitley scores 14 to spark Southern over Alabama A&M 73-64
article.linkText: Whitley scores 14 to spark Southern over Alabama A&M 73-64
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. -- — Brion Whitley came off the bench to score 14 points to guide Southern to a 73-64 win over Alabama A&M on Saturday. Terrell Williams had 12 points and nine rebounds for the Jaguars (13-9, 7-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who have won seven straight at home. Isaiah Rollins and P.J. Byrd scored 11 apiece with Byrd adding six assists. Garrett Hicks scored a season-high 25 points for the Bulldogs (5-15, 4-6). Jalen Johnson added 19 points and 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Portions of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
